            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "AST SpaceMobile, Inc. (NASDAQ:ASTS) saw an increase in premarket trading on Friday after receiving Special Temporary Authority (STA) from the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) for testing in the U.S. This approval allows AST SpaceMobile's first five commercial BlueBird satellites, currently in low Earth orbit, to operate with standard smartphones using AT&T and Verizon's low-band spectrum. The testing will enable voice calls, data, video applications, and other cellular broadband functions without the need for special software or device updates. The FCC's approval aligns with AST SpaceMobile's goals of expanding digital access, improving emergency communications, and advancing digital transformation.",
